    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Stachys africana are fever, which is reduced with its antipyretic properties, and indigestion, caused by its ability to inhibit H+/K+ ATPase in the stomach. It is also used to treat eczema due to its anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial effects. Additionally, the plant's antioxidant properties help to prevent cell damage and oxidative stress, making it effective against asthma by reducing inflammation in the airways. Furthermore, Stachys africana has been shown to exhibit antibacterial activity against certain strains of bacteria, including those responsible for infections such as conjunctivitis. Its anti-inflammatory properties also alleviate the symptoms of rhinitis by reducing swelling in the nasal passages.",
