    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Stachys africana are anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antioxidant, which have been attributed to its bioactive compounds, including flavonoids, phenolic acids, and volatile oils. The anti-inflammatory property of Stachys africana has been linked to the reduction of inflammation and pain, making it a potential treatment for conditions such as arthritis. The antimicrobial property of this plant has been shown to inhibit the growth of bacteria and fungi, making it a useful agent for wound healing and preventing infections. Additionally, the antioxidant property of Stachys africana has been found to protect cells from oxidative damage and may contribute to its potential anticancer effects. The bioactive compounds responsible for these properties, such as saponins and glycosides, have been isolated and characterized in various studies.",
