    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Stachys africana are tea, infusion, tincture, salve, and decoction. Stachys africana tea is made by steeping the leaves in hot water to treat digestive issues and fever. Infusions involve steeping the plant in cold water for a longer period to prepare a soothing drink for colds and respiratory problems. Tinctures are concentrated extracts of the plant in ethanol or glycerol, used in small doses to treat coughs and sore throats. Decoctions of Stachys africana are used in traditional medicine to treat various ailments, including fever, rheumatism, and skin conditions.",
